cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DS

This paper discusses the management of IoT traffic using SDN and QoS-aware frameworks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also mentions dynamic network management and programming technologies like SDN, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of QoS and traffic management also implies that it could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a framework for IoT traffic orchestration, which could also fall under the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
